Date: Thu, 29 May 2008 11:33:49
From: Lesley Stirling [lesleyfs@unimelb.edu.au]
Subject: HCSNet Workshop on Narrative & Communication Disorders
E-mail this message to a friend:
http://linguistlist.org/issues/emailmessage/verification.cfm?iss=19-1718.html&submissionid=180081&topicid=3&msgnumber=1  

Full Title: HCSNet Workshop on Narrative & Communication Disorders 

Date: 13-Sep-2008 - 14-Sep-2008
Location: Melbourne, VIC, Australia 
Contact Person: Lesley Stirling
Meeting Email: lesleyfs@unimelb.edu.au
Web Site: http://www.hcsnet.edu.au/hcsnetevents/2008/ncdworkshop 

Linguistic Field(s): Cognitive Science; Discourse Analysis; Language
Acquisition; Psycholinguistics 

Call Deadline: 02-Jun-2008 

Meeting Description:

The aim of the workshop is to bring together Australian and international
researchers with an interest in narrative and communication disorders. The
workshop will address developmental and acquired disorders of both child and
adult language and perspectives from neurotypical populations; it will consider
topics in theory, methodology and analysis. The intention is to take a truly
interdisciplinary approach, involving speakers and participants from a range of
areas covered by the broad domain of cognitive science, and to generate fruitful
leads and directions for further research. Thus we expect that researchers from
linguistics, psychology, speech pathology, psychiatry, computer science,
cognitive neuroscience and other areas will find the workshop of interest. 

Call for Papers

Interested researchers are invited to submit 200-250 word abstracts for paper or
poster presentations by 2nd June 2008.
Further details are available on the workshop website at
http://www.hcsnet.edu.au/hcsnetevents/2008/ncdworkshop.
For further information please contact Associate Professor Lesley Stirling
lesleyfs@unimelb.edu.au or Dr Susan Douglas sdouglas@unimelb.edu.au.
In view of the late posting of this call, there is some flexibility about the
due date for abstracts: please contact the organizers.



	
